However, these individual bit definitions (rtcCalib, safeBoot, jammingState, xtalAbsent) are present elsewhere in the manual (on page 2, above the MON-HW2 payload), and their combined bit length fits within an X1 (1-byte) field, making the canonical interpretation plausible and common for u-blox manuals.

These additional fields in the canonical are similar in name and offset to fields mentioned in the *general description* (not payload table) of UBX-MON-HW2 on page 2 (e.g., 'cwSuppression' at offset 45). It's plausible the canonical reflects a more complete, albeit deprecated, structure that is only partially documented in the PDF's primary UBX-MON-HW table.
